The BeanInfo is OK now but there is a problem with codegen decoding so if you 
have a line 
jList.setModel(new MyModel());
it throws an IllegalArgumentException
The problem is AttributeFeatureMapper has some hard coded method names that it 
deals with specially.  One of these is setModel.  It returns the one for 
JTable.  This hardcoding needs thought, because even for the other methods 
that are hard coded (there are a few in the map) they must be qualified by the 
class that they belong to somehow, otherwise setModel or setBounds (which is 
another one) are all going to assume that they inherit the one in the table 
when in fact they don't
Reassign to Gili as it is a codegen thing but I'd like to learn more about the 
special methods and maybe code the fix myself once we design a fix
/**
 * The assumption is that it is a vanilla attribute, and a PropertyDecorator 
exists
 */
protected boolean isHardCodedMethod (String method) {
	if (method==null) return false;
	for (int i = 0; i < hardCodeMethods.length; i++) {
		if (method.equals(hardCodeMethods[i])) return true ;
	}
	return false ;
}
